%20is%20hardly%20a%20diagnosis%2C%20even%20when%20those%20memes%20feel%20like%20they%20were%20made%20with%20me%20in%20mind.%20Now%20that%20I've%20seen%20a%20specialist%20who%20confirmed%20my%20suspicions%2C%20the%20feeling%20of%20vindication%20is%20kind%20of%20exhilarating.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af2e8ad5-8c3e-4dbf-aaa6-45b42a1c74a0%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20suspected%20I%20had%20ADHD%20for%20about%2010%20years%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20was%20the%20first%20time%20you%20suspected%20this%3F%26quot%3B%20the%20doctor%20asked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETen%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20was%20team-marking%20with%20other%20teachers%2C%20trapped%20for%20a%20full%20weekend%20with%20the%20task%20of%20grading%20hundreds%20of%20senior%20exams%20before%20the%20deadline.%20The%20other%20teachers%20were%20flying%20through%20essays%2C%20their%20red%20pens%20a%20blur.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20watched%20them%20for%20a%20bit%2C%20wondering%20how%20they%20were%20able%20to%20tune%20each%20other%20out.%20I%20graded%20two%20essays%20and%20then%20made%20some%20tea.%20I%20rewarded%20myself%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fenglish-teacher-my-students-relying-on-ai-for-everything-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinishing%20another%20essay%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20the%20slow%20removal%20of%20my%20jacket.%20Many%20buttons.%20Thrilling.%20And%20then%20one%20more%20essay%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20snack.%20The%20sound%20of%20my%20colleagues'%20pens%20was%20distracting.%20The%20sound%20of%20the%20kettle%20boiling%2C%20even%20more%20so.%20Speaking%20of%20which%E2%80%A6more%20tea%3F%20A%20bathroom%20break%3F%20I%20was%20bored%20senseless.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BHow%20many%20have%20you%20done%2C%20Tayla%3F%26quot%3B%20I'd%20tackled%20four%20in%20the%20time%20the%20others%20had%20each%20graded%2012.%20I%20told%20myself%20it%20was%20because%20the%20other%20teachers%20were%20more%20experienced.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a7895612-3b98-4c24-85eb-1235b4943127%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20developed%20coping%20mechanisms%20long%20ago%20to%20mask%20symptoms%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20shared%20the%20news%20of%20my%20diagnosis%20with%20a%20friend%20from%20school.%20%26quot%3BSeriously%3F%20But%E2%80%A6you're%20so%20productive%3F%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20shocked.%20It%20was%20easy%20to%20slip%20through%20the%20cracks%20as%20a%20high%20achiever.%20ADHD%20diagnoses%20are%20often%20missed%20in%20girls%20%E2%80%94%20the%20ratio%20of%20boys%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwoman-adult-adhd-diagnosis-symptoms-lose-jobs-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egirls%20with%20ADHD%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20is%203%3A1%20in%20childhood%2C%20but%20in%20adulthood%20it's%20much%20closer%20to%201%3A1.%20Apparently%2C%20girls%20with%20ADHD%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20mask%20symptoms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20got%20straight%20As%20in%20school%20(bar%20physical%20science%2C%20which%20felt%20like%20torture)%20and%20graduated%20from%20university%20%3Cem%3Emagna%20cum%20laude%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Along%20the%20way%2C%20I'd%20unknowingly%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fadhd-powerful-tips-tricks-hacks-for-coping-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeveloping%20coping%20strategies%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20weaving%20them%20into%20my%20daily%20life.%20A%20major%20one%20was%20the%20subjects%20I%20chose.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20high%20school%2C%20I%20dropped%20two%20math%20classes%20in%20my%20final%20year%3B%20it%20wasn't%20my%20strong%20suit.%20In%20university%2C%20excelling%20in%20psychology%20and%20English%20was%20easy%20%E2%80%94%20I%20loved%20both%20majors%20and%20would%20happily%20fixate%20on%20them%20for%20hours.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI've%20had%20a%20daily%20to-do%20list%20for%20decades.%20I%20voice%20note%20myself%20constantly.%20My%20calendar%20is%20so%20detailed%20that%20it%20looks%20encyclopedic.%20I%20schedule%20meetings%20and%20my%20toughest%20tasks%20during%20my%20most%20productive%20hours.%20I%20lock%20my%20phone%20away%20during%20work%20because%20I'll%20scroll%20fruitlessly.%20And%20now%20I%20can%20see%20all%20of%20this%20for%20what%20it%20is%3A%20a%20plethora%20of%20coping%20mechanisms.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20pursuing%20my%20writing%20career%2C%20I%20curated%20it%20around%20an%20ADHD%20diagnosis%20I%20didn't%20yet%20have.%20I%20struggle%20to%20write%20on%20topics%20I%20don't%20care%20about%2C%20so%20I%20built%20a%20roster%20of%20clients%20and%20publications%20in%20travel%2C%20a%20subject%20that%20obsesses%20me.%20Being%20self-employed%20has%20allowed%20me%20to%20tap%20into%20other%20interests%2C%20like%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscribblingsidehustlers.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoaching%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20writing%20personal%20essays.%20I've%20always%20gravitated%20toward%20the%20form.%20After%20a%20quick%20Google%2C%20it%20turns%20out%20many%20associate%20oversharing%20with%20ADHD%2C%20too.%20Hmm.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI'm%20throwing%20myself%20into%20learning.%20I'm%20reading%20books%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmy-kids-have-adhd-what-learned-from-experts-2022-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethriving%20with%20ADHD%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20I'm%20following%20relevant%20accounts%20on%20social%20media%2C%20knowing%20that%20I%20now%20belong%20in%20these%20communities.%20The%20best%20time%20to%20get%20this%20diagnosis%20was%20probably%2025%20years%20ago.%20But%20I%20have%20it%20now.%20I'm%20not%20convinced%20this%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bbeginning%20of%20wisdom%26quot%3B%20as%20Aristotle%20says%2C%20but%20it's%20t