s%20a%20sex%20offender.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%20and%20Friday%2C%20Justice%20Department%20officials%20met%20with%20Maxwell%20near%20the%20Florida%20prison%20where%20she's%20serving%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghislaine-maxwell-sentenced-20-years-prison-sex-trafficking-jeffrey-epstein-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E20-year%20sentence%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETheories%20about%20Epstein%20are%20rooted%20in%20mistrust%3A%20Epstein's%20life%20and%20death%20represent%20failures%20of%20the%20institutions%20that%20were%20supposed%20to%20bring%20him%20to%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20conspiracy%20theories%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Earound%20intelligence%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Emake%20hay%20of%20his%20connections%20without%20offering%20much%20evidence%20beyond%20them.%20They%20note%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20that%20Ghislaine%20Maxwell's%20father%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghislaine-maxwell-father-epstein-family-history-yacht-images-2019-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20late%20British%20business%20tycoon%20Robert%20Maxwell%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20is%20widely%20believed%20to%20have%20worked%20for%20Israeli%20intelligence.%20Barak%20visited%20Epstein's%20Manhattan%20townhouse%20on%20multiple%20occasions%20after%20Barak%20left%20office%20%E2%80%94%20something%20the%20former%20prime%20minister%20later%20said%20he%20regretted%20%E2%80%94%20and%20Epstein%20was%20an%20investor%20in%20one%20of%20Barak's%20companies.%20Burns%20also%20met%20multiple%20times%20with%20Epstein%20while%20he%20was%20deputy%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20but%20before%20he%20led%20the%20CIA.%20A%20CIA%20spokesperson%20said%20the%20meetings%20were%20arranged%20so%20that%20Epstein%20could%20offer%20Burns%20career%20advice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20specific%20claims%20that%20are%20often%20cited%20to%20make%20the%20case%20that%20Epstein%20was%20an%20intelligence%20asset%20have%20been%20contradicted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20comes%20from%20a%202019%20opinion%20column%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedailybeast.com%2Fjeffrey-epsteins-sick-story-played-out-for-years-in-plain-sight%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDaily%20Beast%3C%2Fa%3E%20written%20by%20journalist%20Vicky%20Ward.%20According%20to%20Ward%2C%20Alex%20Acosta%2C%20the%20Florida%20prosecutor%20who%20gave%20Epstein%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Falex-acosta-stepping-down-amid-epstein-controversy-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esweetheart%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20mid-2000s%20that%20allowed%20him%20to%20serve%20a%20light%20jail%20sentence%20despite%20law%20enforcement's%20belief%20that%20he%20had%20abused%20dozens%20of%20girls%2C%20was%20asked%20about%20the%20case%20during%20his%20vetting%20to%20be%20named%20labor%20secretary%20during%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20told%20Epstein%20'belonged%20to%20intelligence'%20and%20to%20leave%20it%20alone%2C%26quot%3B%20Acosta%20said%2C%20according%20to%20Ward's%20anonymous%20source.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcosta%20said%20the%20opposite%20when%20he%20spoke%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department's%20Office%20of%20Professional%20Responsibility%20for%20a%20report%20published%20in%202020.%20Asked%20whether%20he%20had%20knowledge%20of%20Epstein%20being%20%26quot%3Ban%20intelligence%20asset%2C%26quot%3B%20Acosta%20told%20them%2C%20%26quot%3Bthe%20answer%20is%20no.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcosta's%20response%20was%20buried%20in%20a%20footnote%20on%20page%20169%20of%20the%20348-page%20report%20and%20was%20not%20widely%20seen.%20Acosta%20declined%20to%20comment%20for%20this%20story.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20told%20what%20I%20was%20told%20and%20the%20person%20who's%20told%20it%20to%20me%20has%20never%20backtracked%20from%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Ward%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-accuser-detailed-sex-with-alan-dershowitz-in-unsealed-document-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAlan%20Dershowitz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20represented%20Epstein%20in%20the%20Florida%20case%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Epstein%20told%20him%20he%20didn't%20have%20ties%20to%20intelligence%20agencies.%20%26quot%3BHe%20said%20'absolutely%20no.'%20He%20said%20he%20wished%20he%20did%2C%20that%20it%20would've%20been%20very%20helpful%26quot%3B%20to%20get%20an%20even%20better%20deal%2C%20Dershowitz%20says.%20%26quot%3BIf%20he%20had%20had%20any%20connection%20to%20any%20governmental%20agency%20whatsoever%2C%20I%20would%20be%20the%20first%20person%20to%20know%20about%20it.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Epstein's%20accusers%2C%20Virginia%20Giuffre%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepstein-accuser-detailed-sex-with-alan-dershowitz-in-unsealed-document-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccused%20Dershowitz%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20abuse%2C%20but%20later%20withdrew%20the%20allegation%20and%20said%20she%20%26quot%3Bmay%20have%20made%20a%20mistake.%26quot%3B%20Dershowitz%20has%20called%20for%20the%20public%20release%20of%20the%20Epstein%20files.%20%26quot%3BThey%20would%20distinguish%20between%20true%20accusations%20and%20false%20accusations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20claim%20involves%20the%20existence%20of%20videos%20%E2%80%94%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Efilmed%20for%20the%20benefit%20of%20Epstein's%20intelligence%20handlers%2C%20the%20theory%20goes%20%E2%80%94%20showing%20Epstein's%20friends%20having%20sex%20with%20underage%20girls.%20Epstein's%20victims%20have%20said%20he%20told%20them%20he%20had%20cameras%20throughout%20his%20homes.%20The%20specific%20claim%20that%20Epstein%20was%20recording%20sexual%20acts%20involving%20his%20associates%20comes%20from%20statements%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fghislaine-maxwell-sentencing-tearful-victims-statements-hearing-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESarah%20Ransome%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20one%20of%20Epstein's%20accusers%2C%20made%20in%202016.%20Ransome%20later%20admitted%20that%20she%20made%20it%20up.%20%26quot%3BI%20was%20absolutely%20terrified%20that%2C%20once%20I%20went%20public%20with%20my%20story%2C%20Jeffrey%20and%20Ghislaine%20would%20find%20and%20kill%20me%2C%26quot%3B%20Ransome%20wrote%20in%20her%202021%20memoir.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20seized%20Epstein%20documents%20contained%20any%20whiff%20of%20intelligence%20ties%2C%20there%20are%20several%20ways%20that%20could%20have%20shown%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20when%20Justice%20Department%20prosecutors%20suspect%20a%20US%20intelligence%20agency%2C%20such%20as%20the%20CIA%20or%20NSA%2C%20might%20have%20information%20pertinent%20to%20a%20criminal%20case%20they're%20investigating%2C%20they%20will%20make%20a%20request%20for%20a%20prudential%20review%2C%20also%20called%20a%20prudential%20search%2C%20experts%20in%20national%20security%20law%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20prudential%20review%20is%20where%20you%20kick%20the%20tires%20and%20make%20sure%20there's%20nothing%20that%20the%20intelligence%20community%20has%20that%20is%20going%20to%20make%20it%20impossible%20or%20unethical%20for%20you%20to%20bring%20your%20case%20because%20you%20can't%20comply%20with%20your%20discovery%20obligations%20because%20the%20information%20is%20classified%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hickey%2C%20who's%20now%20a%20defense%20attorney%20with%20the%20firm%20Mayer%20Brown.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20no%20indication%20that%20a%20prudential%20review%20ever%20took%20place%2C%20according%20to%20the%20four%20people%20who%20had%20access%20to%20the%20records%20seized%20by%20the%20FBI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Epstein's%20case%2C%20the%20reason%20for%20this%20might%20have%20come%20down%20to%20timing%2C%20two%20of%20his%20lawyers%20told%20BI%3A%20His%20death%2C%20mere%20weeks%20after%20his%20arrest%2C%20meant%20there%20wasn't%20much%20time%20to%20process%20the%20evidence%20against%20him.%20%26quot%3BBecause%20Epstein%20died%20very%20early%20on%2C%20the%20government%20had%20produced%20little%20discovery%20and%20our%20primary%20initial%20focus%20was%20bail%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20of%20those%20lawyers%20in%20the%202019%20case%2C%20Marc%20Fernich%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20memoir%2C%20Geoffrey%20Berman%2C%20the%20US%20attorney%20who%20oversaw%20the%20case%20against%20Epstein%2C%20wrote%20that%20his%20team%20never%20met%20with%20Epstein's%20defense%20team%20to%20discuss%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20plea%20deal.%20%26quot%3BEpstein%20had%20one%20condition%3A%20he%20wanted%20assurances%20that%20the%20SDNY%20did%20not%20see%20him%20as%20a%20rapist%2C%26quot%3B%20Berman%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThat%20was%20the%20end%20of%20that.%20He%20was%20a%20rapist%2C%20and%20we%20were%20not%20about%20to%20give%20him%20some%20other%2C%20more%20polite-sounding%20label.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20no%20indication%20that%20a%20prudential%20review%20was%20requested%20in%20the%20case%20against%20Maxwell%2C%20which%20involved%20much%20of%20the%20same%20evidence%20collected%20for%20Epstein's%20prosecution%2C%20the%20four%20people%20said.%20A%20representative%20for%20the%20US%20Attorney's%20office%20in%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20New%20York%20and%20an%20attorney%20for%20Maxwell%20declined%20to%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20there's%20no%20record%20of%20evidence%20being%20removed%20for%20national%20security%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20prosecutors%20to%20remove%20certain%20pieces%20of%20evidence%2C%20to%20avoid%20exposing%20sensitive%20intelligence%20to%20defense%20attorneys%2C%20they%20would%20need%20to%20file%20motions%20under%20the%20Classified%20Information%20Procedures%20Act%2C%20or%20CIPA.%20The%20motions%20would%20be%20noted%20on%20the%20public%20court%20docket%2C%20experts%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20way%20things%20normally%20happen%20is%20that%20there%20would%20be%20some%20tell%20in%20the%20docket%20that%20you're%20dealing%20with%20these%20issues%2C%20and%20the%20court%20knows%20about%20it%20through%20CIPA%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Hickey.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECIPA%20was%20enacted%20in%201980%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20to%20prosecute%20people%20with%20intelligence%20ties.%20Until%20then%2C%20legal%20experts%20say%2C%20defendants%20with%20such%20ties%20could%20use%20the%20threat%20of%20exposing%20government%20secrets%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bgraymail%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20it%20was%20called%20%E2%80%94%20to%20avoid%20prosecution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBefore%20CIPA%2C%20basically%20nobody%20would%20ever%20prosecute%20CIA%20officers%20because%20they%20would%20always%20pull%20this%20shit%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Kel%20McClanahan%2C%20a%20national%20security%20attorney%20and%20law%20professor%20at%20George%20Washington%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBI's%20search%20of%20the%20docket%20for%20the%20federal%20cases%20against%20Epstein%20or%20Maxwell%20found%20no%20mention%20of%20CIPA%20litigation.%20No%20member%20of%20Maxwell's%20high-powered%20defense%20team%20%E2%80%94%20which%20included%20lawyers%20who%20have%20worked%20on%20cases%20involving%20terrorists%20and%20international%20drug%20traffickers%20%E2%80%94%20asked%20the%20judge%20to%20order%20prosecutors%20to%20conduct%20a%20prudential%20search%20of%20intelligence%20agency%20material.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20it's%20true%20that%20there%20was%20never%20a%20search%20for%20government%20secrets%20or%20arguments%20for%20pulling%20evidence%2C%20and%20if%20no%20links%20to%20intelligence%20ever%20emerged%20from%20extensive%20reviews%20of%20the%20Epstein%20files%2C%20it%20does%20not%20%26quot%3Bdefinitively%20remove%20the%20question%26quot%3B%20of%20an%20intelligence%20role%2C%20McClanahan%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20a%20%26quot%3Bpretty%20damn%20convincing%26quot%3B%20sign%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fjacob-shamsian%5C