and%20Parbhani%2C%20has%20seen%20widespread%20adoption%20of%20this%20variety%E2%80%94followed%20by%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F389465%2Fparmeshwar-thorat-avocado-organic-farming-drought-beed-maharashtra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFarmers%20also%20praise%20its%20high%20yields%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20can%20go%20up%20to%2010%20tonnes%20per%20acre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBut%20who%20developed%20the%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%20sat%20down%20with%2067-year-old%20farmer%20innovator%20Navnath%20Kaspate%2C%20the%20mind%20behind%20this%20unique%20variety.%20In%202019%2C%20his%20innovation%20earned%20him%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20from%20the%20Protection%20of%20Plant%20Varieties%20and%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(PPV%26amp%3BRA).%20Today%2C%20he%20owns%20a%2070-acre%20farm%E2%80%94Madhuban%20Farm%20and%20Nursery%E2%80%94which%20is%20home%20to%2042%20different%20varieties%20of%20custard%20apples.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ETracing%20the%20history%20of%20Golden%20Sitaphal%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBelonging%20to%20the%20Annonaceae%20family%2C%20custard%20apple%E2%80%94heart-shaped%2C%20spherical%2C%20or%20irregular%E2%80%94features%20quilted%20skin%20that%20turns%20brown%20as%20it%20ripens.%20Originally%20from%20South%20America%20and%20the%20West%20Indies%2C%20Sitaphal%20was%20introduced%20to%20India%20by%20the%20Portuguese%20in%20the%2016th%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERemarkably%2C%20depictions%20of%20custard%20apples%20appear%20in%20ancient%20Indian%20sculptures%2C%20such%20as%20those%20at%20Bharhut%2C%20Sanchi%2C%20Ajanta%2C%20and%20Mathura%2C%20dating%20back%20to%20the%202nd%20century%20BCE.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20varieties%20like%20Balanagar%2C%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20and%20Lal%20Sitaphal%20exist%2C%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20is%20expanding%20rapidly%20due%20to%20its%20strong%20market%20acceptance%20and%20profitability%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStarted%20by%20one%20innovator%2C%20many%20followed%20suit%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20dryland%20crop%2C%20custard%20apple%20requires%20minimal%20irrigation%E2%80%94especially%20in%20the%20first%20two%20years%E2%80%94and%20is%20well-suited%20for%20drip%20irrigation%2C%20resulting%20in%20fewer%20pest%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-1536x1152.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470-150x113.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470.jpg%201600w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476011%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22375%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EMany%20farmers%20and%20experts%20praise%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20for%20its%20high%20yield%2C%20larger%20fruit%20size%2C%20fewer%20seeds%2C%20and%20better%20market%20prices.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaspate%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20grow%20grapes%20and%20ber%2C%20but%20after%20developing%20NMK-01%2C%20I%20converted%20my%20entire%20farm%20to%20Sitaphal%2C%20inspiring%20others%20to%20follow.%E2%80%9D%20Farmers%20in%20five%20talukas%E2%80%94Barshi%2C%20Khamgaon%2C%20Ghormale%2C%20Kasarwadi%2C%20and%20Wanewadi%E2%80%94took%20to%20the%20charm%20of%20custard%20apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Barshi%20taluka%20alone%2C%20140%20villages%20now%20cultivate%20custard%20apple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWhy%20Is%20NMK-01%20Golden%20Sitaphal%20the%20most%20preferred%20variety%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20173%20accepted%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%3C%2Fem%3E%20species%20worldwide%2C%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%2070-acre%20Madhuban%20Farm%20and%20Nursery%20is%20like%20a%20living%20museum.%20You%20can%20find%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20glabra%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EPink%E2%80%99s%20Mammoth%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20muricata%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EIcecal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EWashington%20Jem%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%3Cem%3EAnnona%20montana%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20many%20more%20on%20his%20farm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20farm%20is%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20nursery%20devoted%20to%20Sitaphal%20and%20also%20serves%20as%20a%20development%20and%20research%20centre.%20Additionally%2C%20he%20hosts%20prospective%20custard%20apple%20growers%20with%20free%20full-day%20workshops%20on%20agronomic%20practices.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20have%20created%20around%203%2C000%20varieties%20using%20the%20process%20of%20cross-pollination.%20These%20cannot%20be%20found%20elsewhere.%20Only%20when%20one%20registers%20a%20variety%20with%20an%20authority%20like%20the%20PPV%20%26amp%3B%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Rights%20Authority%20(FRA)%2C%20can%20it%20be%20officially%20recognised.%20I%20have%20selected%20some%20of%20them%2C%20filed%20for%20patents%2C%20and%20started%20acquiring%20Intellectual%20Property%20Rights%20(IPR).%20In%20India%2C%20living%20things%20like%20plants%20and%20animals%2C%20and%20the%20natural%20processes%20used%20to%20produce%20them%2C%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20patented%E2%80%94but%20they%20can%20receive%20other%20forms%20of%20IPR%20protection%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESolapur%E2%80%99s%20Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra%20highlights%20several%20of%20his%20innovative%20custard%20apple%20varieties%3A%20Annona-2%2C%20NMK-1%2C%20NMK-2%2C%20NMK-3%2C%20and%20Finger%20Prints.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%20most%20popular%20varieties%20is%20NMK-1%2C%20which%20he%20began%20developing%20in%202002.%20Farmers%20love%20it%20for%20its%20attractive%20colour%20and%20size%2C%20the%20good%20number%20of%20fruits%20each%20plant%20produces%2C%20and%20its%20uniform%20shape%E2%80%94making%20it%20ideal%20for%20export.%20The%20fruits%20also%20stay%20unripe%20on%20the%20plant%20for%2020%E2%80%9325%20days%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20crack%20after%20harvesting%2C%20and%20suffer%20fewer%20losses%20during%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EComparing%20varieties%3A%20market%20research%2C%20pricing%2C%20yield%2C%20taste%2C%20and%20farmer%20preference%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaharashtra%20leads%20custard%20apple%20production%20in%20India%2C%20with%20other%20popular%20varieties%20like%20Lal%20Sitaphal%2C%20Balanagari%2C%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%20also%20grown%20here.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOut%20of%20the%2055%2C000%20hectares%20of%20custard%20apple%20farms%20in%20India%2C%207%2C000%20hectares%20are%20in%20Maharashtra%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustard%20apples%20are%20traded%20daily%20in%20and%20outside%20the%20state%2C%20with%20supplies%20reaching%20markets%20in%20Mumbai%2C%20Pune%2C%20Hyderabad%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20and%20Delhi.%20From%20market%20yards%20in%20Pune%20and%20Navi%20Mumbai%2C%20the%20creamy%2C%20grainy-fleshed%20fruit%20is%20distributed%20to%20fruit%20stalls%20and%20malls%20in%20major%20cities%20across%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompared%20to%20Balanagar%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar%2C%20NMK-01%20yields%20up%20to%2012%20tonnes%20per%20acre%20(versus%20five%20to%20six%20tonnes)%20and%20commands%20a%20higher%20price.%20However%2C%20while%20its%20appearance%20and%20sweetness%20appeal%20to%20many%2C%20some%20growers%20and%20consumers%20find%20its%20flavour%20less%20desirable%20than%20local%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20970px)%20100vw%2C%20970px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22970%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465.jpg%20970w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-500x375.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-768x576.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FMhow-custard-apple-grower-in-his-farm_11zon-1753429465-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476010%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22728%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EMaharashtra%20leads%20custard%20apple%20production%20in%20India%2C%20with%20other%20popular%20varieties%20like%20Lal%20Sitaphal%2C%20Balanagari%2C%20and%20Phule%20Purandhar.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENMK-01%20is%20sweeter%20and%20visually%20attractive%2C%20but%20several%20people%20describe%20its%20taste%20as%20different%20or%20less%20appealing%E2%80%94possibly%20due%20to%20its%20hybrid%20origin%20with%20Atemoya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F407624%2Fkrushi-sarathi-app-for-farmers-in-maharashtra%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMany%20farmers%20%3C%2Fa%3Eand%20experts%20praise%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20for%20its%20high%20yield%2C%20larger%20fruit%20size%2C%20fewer%20seeds%2C%20and%20better%20market%20prices.%20Reports%20show%20that%20this%20variety%20can%20double%20production%20and%20significantly%20increase%20income%2C%20with%20some%20farmers%20earning%20up%20to%20Rs%2012%20lakh%20per%20hectare%20and%20market%20prices%20reaching%20Rs%20200%20to%20Rs%20300%20per%20kg.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbout%20six%20years%20ago%2C%2035-year-old%20Ravi%20Dabhade%20from%20Jerai%20village%20in%20Maharashtra%E2%80%99s%20Beed%20district%20planted%20around%206%2C000%20NMK-01%20custard%20apple%20saplings%20across%2012%20acres%20of%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEncouraged%20by%20the%20success%2C%20he%20expanded%20cultivation%20by%20another%20four%20acres%20a%20few%20years%20later.%20Today%2C%20his%20orchard%20spans%20nearly%2020%20acres%2C%20yielding%20an%20impressive%20seven%20tonnes%20per%20acre.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20500px)%20100vw%2C%20500px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-500x667.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Golden%20Sitaphal%20farmer%20innovator%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-500x667.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-225x300.jpg%20225w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-768x1024.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-640x853.jpg%20640w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459-150x200.jpg%20150w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FKaspate-in-his-nursery-with-a-custard-apple-sapling_11zon-1753429459.jpg%201149w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-476009%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKaspate%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20grow%20grapes%20and%20ber%2C%20but%20after%20developing%20NMK-01%2C%20I%20converted%20my%20entire%20farm%20to%20Sitaphal%2C%20inspiring%20others%20to%20follow.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERavi%20attributes%20his%20high%20productivity%20to%20disciplined%20crop%20management%2C%20especially%20eight%20annual%20foliar%20sprays%20that%20keep%20pests%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20in%202018%2C%2055-year-old%20Dinesh%20Patidar%20from%20Jamli%20village%20in%20Mhow%20Cantonment%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20planted%204%2C800%20saplings%20sourced%20from%20Madhuban%20across%2012%20acres.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20grow%20a%20mix%20of%20fruits%20like%20mango%2C%20dragon%20fruit%2C%20guava%2C%20and%20avocado.%20Sitaphal%20starts%20bearing%20fruit%20in%20October%2C%20and%20the%20harvest%20continues%20through%20mid-January.%20I%20typically%20get%20four%20to%20five%20tonnes%20per%20acre%2C%20bringing%20in%20a%20profit%20of%20around%20Rs%201.5%20lakh%20per%20acre%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ENew%20varieties%20and%20the%20road%20ahead%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaspate%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CIt%20has%20taken%20me%20close%20to%2012%20years%20to%20develop%20the%20new%20varieties%E2%80%94NMK%20Arvi%20and%20NMK%20Samruddhi.%20Arvi%20is%20a%20cross%20between%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%20and%20Lal%20Sitaphal%2C%20while%20the%20red-coloured%20Samruddhi%20is%20a%20mix%20of%20Sitaphal%20and%20Ramphal%20(%3Cem%3EAnnona%20reticulata%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Both%20are%20harvested%20in%20February.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CSince%20December%202021%2C%20NMK%20Samruddhi%20has%20been%20tested%20over%20six%20harvests.%20On%20average%2C%20each%20fruit%20weighed%20350%20grams%2C%20had%2060%25%20pulp%2C%20and%20a%20sweetness%20level%20(Brix)%20of%2025%E2%80%94making%20it%20a%20favourite%20among%20both%20farmers%20and%20buyers.%20NMK%20Arvi%20also%20showed%20similar%20results%2C%20with%20350-gram%20fruits%2C%2055%25%20pulp%2C%20fewer%20seeds%2C%20and%20the%20same%20sweetness.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaspate%20has%20distributed%20saplings%20for%20trials%20to%20farmers%20in%20Ghormale%20and%20Barshi%20talukas%20and%20plans%20to%20launch%20the%20new%20varieties%20once%20he%20secures%20IPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20submitted%20the%20documents%20about%20the%20newly%20developed%20varieties%20to%20PPV%26amp%3BRA%20in%20November%202023.%20I%20will%20introduce%20them%20to%20farmers%20soon%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20challenge%20of%20counterfeiting%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20on%20new%20varieties%2C%20Kaspate%20continues%20to%20battle%20counterfeiters%E2%80%94a%20major%20challenge%20for%20farmer-innovators%20in%20India.%20Many%20nurseries%20sell%20unauthorised%20saplings%20under%20different%20names%20to%20hide%20their%20origin%2C%20but%20they%20are%20all%20NMK-01%20(Golden)%2C%20for%20which%20Kaspate%20holds%20the%20IPR.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20filed%20cases%20in%20the%20Solapur%20District%20Court%20against%20220%20nurseries%20for%20selling%20counterfeits%20and%20has%20paid%20Rs%2015%20lakhs%20in%20stamp%20duty%20for%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20every%20breakthrough%2C%20Kaspate%20not%20only%20uplifts%20his%20community%20but%20redefines%20what%20it%20means%20to%20farm%20with%20purpose%20in%20dryland%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAll%20images%20courtesy%20Hiren%20Bose%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1753450921000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FNMK-Arvi_11zon-1753429470.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D475953%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Navnath%20Kaspate%E2%80%99s%20breakthrough%20custard%20apple%20varieties%20are%20transforming%20drought-prone%20farming%2C%20doubling%20yields%2C%20and%20inspiring%20thousands.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Hiren%20Kumar%20Bose%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F475953%2Ffarmer-innovator-golden-sitaphal-custard-apple-navnath-kaspate-maharashtra-madhya-pradesh%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20Bengaluru%20Startup%20Built%20a%20Machine%20That%20Turns%20Waste%20Into%20Nutrient-Rich%20Compost%20in%20Just%208%20Hours%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ffactly.in%2Freview-municipal-solid-waste-generated-in-india-set-to-increase-7-times-in-the-next-30-years%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCurrently%252C%2520as%2520per%2520government%2520estimates%2C%252C%2520wood%252C%2520glass%252C%2520etc.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egovernment%20estimates%3C%2Fa%3E%20dating%20back%20to%202021%2C%20India%20generates%20more%20than%2062%20million%20tonnes%20of%20Municipal%20Solid%20Waste%20(MSW)%2C%20of%20which%20approximately%2075-80%25%20gets%20collected.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20amount%20of%20MSW%20collected%2C%20only%20about%2022-28%25%20is%20processed%20and%20treated.%20The%20rest%20ends%20up%20in%20landfills.%20Going%20further%2C%20up%20to%20half%20the%20MSW%20collected%20in%20India%20consists%20of%20%E2%80%9Cbiodegradable%20(organic)%20matter%E2%80%9D%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmohua.gov.in%2Fupload%2Fuploadfiles%2Ffiles%2F93.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMinistry%20of%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20scale%20of%20this%20problem%2C%20there%20are%20multiple%20ventures%20across%20different%20Indian%20cities%20arriving%20at%20different%20scalable%20solutions%20to%20treat%20organic%20MSW.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20%E2%80%98Waste%20Is%20Gold%E2%80%99%2C%20a%20Bengaluru-based%20waste%20management%20company%2C%20is%20one%20such%20venture%20which%20has%20arrived%20at%20a%20unique%20technological%20solution%20to%20address%20this%20pressing%20waste%20management%20concern.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalled%20the%20%E2%80%98Gold%20Composter%E2%80%99%2C%20their%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F301152%2Fbengaluru-designer-builds-home-composter-mess-free-odourless-daily-dump-waste-composting%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganic%20waste%20composter%3C%2Fa%3E%20possesses%20an%20impressive%20capability%20of%20%E2%80%9Cseamlessly%20converting%E2%80%9D%20waste%20amounting%20to%20anywhere%20between%2020%20kg%20to%2010%20tonnes%20into%20%E2%80%98nutrient-rich%20compost%E2%80%99%20in%20just%20eight%20hours%20%E2%80%9Cwithout%20emitting%20harmful%20emissions%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESandeep%20Tiwari%2C%20founder%20of%20Waste%20Is%20Gold%20Technologies%2C%20calls%20the%20Gold%20Composter%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmarvel%20of%20waste%20management%20technology%E2%80%9D.%20Speaking%20to%20%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20innovation%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20there.%20We%20have%20the%20expertise%20and%20versatility%20to%20design%20and%20implement%20large%20composters%20that%20can%20process%20hundreds%20of%20tons%20of%20organic%20waste%20in%20a%20single%20day%20as%20well.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sandeep%20Tiwari%2C%20CEO%20of%20Waste%20Is%20Gold%20Technologies.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2FWaste-Is-Gold-Technologies-CEO-1695133545-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-330329%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESandeep%20Tiwari%2C%20CEO%20of%20Waste%20Is%20Gold%20Technologies.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EHow%20Does%20It%20Work%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Tiwari%2C%20the%20Gold%20Composter%20is%20an%20advanced%20aerobic%20organic%20waste%20composter%20which%20%E2%80%9Cemploys%20a%20completely%20natural%20bio-mechanical%20process%2C%20harnessing%20the%20power%20of%20our%20proprietary%20bacteria%20and%20bioreactor%20technology%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20approach%20breaks%20down%20organic%20waste%20rapidly%2C%20eliminating%20the%20need%20for%20excessive%20heating%20and%20ensuring%20that%20no%20harmful%20emissions%20like%20methane%20are%20released%20into%20the%20environment.%20This%20results%20in%20a%20composting%20process%20with%20a%20low%20carbon%20footprint.%20Operating%20on%20the%20principles%20of%20aerobic%20decomposition%2C%20this%20cutting-edge%20technology%20employs%20oxygen-consuming%20microorganisms%20and%20bio-reactor%20to%20accelerate%20the%20breakdown%20of%20organic%20matter%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20explains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20machine%20facilitates%20aerobic%20composting%20by%20meticulously%20maintaining%20the%20ideal%20temperature%2C%20air%2C%20oxygen%2C%20and%20moisture%20conditions%2C%20guaranteeing%20a%20fast%20and%20efficient%20transformation%20of%20organic%20waste.%20Our%20organic%20waste%20composter%20output%20requires%20no%20further%20processing.%20It%20can%20be%20directly%20placed%20into%20aerated%20crates%20for%20storage%2C%20ready%20for%20later%20use%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20agricultural%20purposes%2C%20Tiwari%20recommends%20allowing%20the%20compost%20to%20fully%20mature%20for%20three%20to%20seven%20days%20after%20processing%2C%20ensuring%20it%20reaches%20its%20peak%20nutrient%20content.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHowever%2C%20for%20landscaping%20and%20gardening%20needs%2C%20the%20compost%20can%20be%20utilised%20on%20the%20same%20day%20it%E2%80%99s%20produced%2C%20providing%20an%20instant%20boost%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F318062%2Fiit-bombay-scientist-dr-rajul-patkar-innovates-portable-soil-testing-device-for-farmers%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esoil%20health%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Our%20composter%20can%20treat%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20organic%20waste%20types%20%E2%80%94%20including%20cooked%20food%20waste%2C%20organic%20wet%20waste%2C%20bones%2C%20meat%2C%20feathers%2C%20eggshells%2C%20vegetable%20waste%2C%20tender%20coconut%2C%20horticulture%20waste%2C%20grass%20clippings%2C%20tissue%20paper%2C%20STP%20sludge%20and%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EFrom%20waste%20to%20compost%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20Solid%20Waste%20Management%20Policy%202016%20mandates%20that%20bulk%20waste%20generators%20take%20responsibility%20for%20processing%20their%20waste%20right%20at%20their%20own%20premises.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20approach%20complements%20this%20policy%20seamlessly.%20By%20deploying%20our%20aerobic%20composter%20directly%20at%20our%20client%E2%80%99s%20premises%2C%20we%20empower%20bulk%20waste%20generators%20to%20comply%20with%20government%20directives.%20This%20not%20only%20eases%20the%20burden%20on%20landfills%20but%20also%20contributes%20to%20a%20cleaner%20environment.%20We%20stand%20as%20reliable%20partners%20for%20communities%2C%20organisations%2C%20urban%20local%20bodies%20and%20institutions%20in%20their%20journey%20towards%20responsible%20waste%20management%20practices%20and%20help%20them%20to%20reduce%20their%20carbon%20footprint%2C%E2%80%9D%20claims%20Tiwari.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20feeding%20organic%20waste%20into%20their%20Gold%20Composter%2C%20a%20crucial%20step%20in%20their%20process%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmeticulous%20resegregation%E2%80%9D%20of%20waste.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20ensures%20that%20no%20inorganic%20materials%20are%20present%20in%20the%20waste%20stream%20before%20it%20undergoes%20processing%20in%20our%20composter.%20This%20meticulous%20sorting%20not%20only%20optimises%20the%20efficiency%20of%20our%20composting%20process%20but%20also%20contributes%20to%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20nutrient-rich%20compost%20produced.%C2%A0%20As%20stated%20earlier%2C%20this%20compost%20can%20be%20utilised%20for%20landscaping%20and%20it%20can%20also%20be%20sold%20to%20farmers%20for%20organic%20farming%20practices.%20By%20closing%20the%20loop%20on%20organic%20waste%2C%20we%20promote%20sustainable%20waste%20management%20and%20foster%20a%20more%20eco-conscious%20and%20economically%20viable%20future%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20claim%20holds%20some%20water%20given%20that%20their%20waste%20composter%20was%20purchased%20by%20the%20Central%20Food%20Technological%20Research%20Institute%20for%20research%20and%20development%20and%20to%20set%20composting%20standards%20across%20India.%20Thus%20far%2C%20their%20composters%20have%20been%20installed%20across%20approximately%20150%20locations%20around%20the%20country%20processing%20about%202%2C500%20tonnes%20of%20waste%20and%20generating%201%2C200%20tonnes%20of%20compost%20per%20month.%20But%20none%20of%20these%20developments%20happened%20overnight.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20took%20around%20five%20years%20of%20extensive%20research%20and%20development%20before%20Waste%20Is%20Gold%20Technologies%20arrived%20at%20its%20flagship%20Gold%20Composter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20journey%20began%20in%202014%20marked%20by%20a%20spirit%20of%20experimentation%20and%20innovation.%20By%202015%2C%20we%20had%20successfully%20developed%20our%20first%20prototype%2C%20a%20pivotal%20milestone%20that%20spurred%20us%20to%20delve%20deeper%20into%20research%20and%20development%20to%20refine%20our%20product%20further.%20Our%20first%20prototype%20transformed%20waste%20into%20compost%20in%2015%20days%20without%20the%20need%20for%20any%20time-consuming%20curing%20process.%20This%20achievement%20set%20us%20apart%20from%20our%20competitors.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20they%20typically%20required%20a%20protracted%2030%20to%2045%20days%20to%20achieve%20the%20same%20results%2C%E2%80%9D%20recalls%20Tiwari.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202018%2C%20his%20venture%20took%20the%20next%20significant%20step%20by%20incorporating%20Waste%20Is%20Gold%20Technologies%20Pvt.%20Ltd.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20developed%20around%2010%20prototypes%20before%20arriving%20at%20our%20Gold%20Composter.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20we%20introduced%20the%20Gold%20Composter%20to%20the%20market.%20Still%20awaiting%20a%20patent%2C%20the%20Gold%20Composter%20